# Copy to `.env` and adjust. `dg dev` auto-loads `.env` from the project root.
#
# Three local-dev strategies, pick one:
#
# ─── (1) Point at shared staging Lambda (recommended for Dagster-side iteration)
LAMBDA_FUNCTION_NAME=lambda-compute-demo-compute-staging
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# Plus AWS_PROFILE or AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID / AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY, however you
# auth into AWS locally (SSO, leapp, etc.).

# ─── (2) Personal CDK stack (recommended when iterating on Lambda code itself)
# Deploy with: `cd infra && cdk deploy -c env=$USER`
# Then set:
# LAMBDA_FUNCTION_NAME=lambda-compute-demo-compute-cdykinski
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1

# ─── (3) Convention-based via the synthetic DAGSTER_CLOUD_DEPLOYMENT_NAME
# If you've deployed a Lambda for a specific "deployment name" via CDK, you
# can just set this and the component will derive the function name:
# DAGSTER_CLOUD_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=staging
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
